TAKE THE FAMILY ALONG!
FLY FIRST CLASS - SAVE MONEY
REDUCED-FARE
FAMILY PLAN
AVAILABLE MONDAY THROUGH THURSDAY
You can travel First Class and save money, by using
United's Reduced-Fare Family Plan. Buy a full-fare
one-way first class ticket for yourself for a flight
departing between 12:01
p.m. Monday and
12:01 p.m. Thursday. Then you can buy tickets, at
two-thirds the cost of the one-way first class fare,
for your wife and/or children 12 through 21 years of
age. Children between 2 and 12 travel for half fare, and
a child under 2 years of age, not occupying
a seat, can travel with your family at no extra cost.
(Plan not effective between California and Hawaii
nor on United Air Coach and Custom Coach flights.)
For reservations, call an authorized travel
agent or
